headline: Retail sales, Alphabet chips for Meta, Dick's earnings: 3 Things
summary: US stock futures (ES=F, NQ=F, YM=F) are mixed in Tuesday's pre-market session after September's retail sales data rose by 0.2% (below economists' forecasts for 0.4% in that month), while September PPI (Producer Price Index) rose 0.3% in the month and 2.7% year-over-year. According to a report from The Information, Meta Platforms (META) is in talks to spend billions on AI chips developed by Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL), putting the Google parent company in a position to directly compete with semiconductor giant Nvidia (NVDA). headline: Retail earnings in focus with Best Buy leading the way
summary: Best Buy (BBY) posted third quarter results that beat Wall Street estimates and raised its full-year outlook, setting the stage for the retailer as it heads into the crucial holiday shopping season. Kohl's (KSS) forecast a smaller drop in sales and bigger profit for the full year, as the U.S. department-store operator banks on new collections and promotions to drive demand during the holiday season, sending its shares surging in the premarket. Meanwhile, share of Dick's Sporting Goods (DKS) fell sharply before the opening bell despite raising its outlook. Investors are more worried about the cost of turning around its recent purchase of Foot Locker. For more live coverage of the markets, watch the full episode of Market Sunrise and visit Yahoo Finance.
